<subSubSection pageId="92" pageNumber="93" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="92.[124,653,193,950]" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">
ETYMOLOGY: The Latin specific epithet 
<taxonomicName authorityName="OPITZ" authorityYear="2005" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Aphelocerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="improcerus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">improcerus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
means undersized. I selected the name because my initial impression of this specimen was that it was a small individual of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Chevrolat)" baseAuthorityName="Chevrolat" box="[159,462,926,950]" class="Insecta" family="Cleridae" genus="Clerus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="92" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="scutellaris">
<emphasis box="[159,315,927,950]" italics="true" pageId="92" pageNumber="93">A. scutellaris</emphasis>
(Chevrolat)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
